cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the modeling and performance analysis of a multi-antenna multi-way channel with UAV-D2D interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their performance. The paper also involves the use of UAVs for communication, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the performance of different transmission schemes, which involves the use of control systems and optimization techniques, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely category. The paper also involves the use of multi-antenna systems, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of UAVs, which involves the use of robotics and autonomous systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) a likely category as well.
